      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Given your previous experience with heartburn, a dull pressure might be a more common interpretation. However, it's still a good idea to wait for a bit to see how your symptoms worsen or improve. Typically, if you have mild to moderate heartburn, antacids can provide relief within 30 minutes to an hour. If your symptoms persist or worsen, or if you experience sharp pain, vomiting, or difficulty breathing, you should consider seeking medical attention.",
      "source": "target",
